@startuml skill-only-enforcement-sequence
!include octo-theme.puml
hide footbox
autonumber

title Skill-only enforcement — every rule travels with the skill

actor User
box "Developer workstation — everything runs locally" #F8F9FB
  participant "Claude Code\n<size:11><i>follows SKILL.md</i></size>" as Agent
  participant "ppg-guard\n<size:11><i>hook (SessionStart,</i></size>\n<size:11><i>PreToolUse Edit|Write)</i></size>" as Guard
  participant "ppg-mcp-server\n<size:11><i>stdio MCP</i></size>" as MCP
  database "Ticket store\n<size:11>$XDG_STATE_HOME/ppg</size>" as Store
  participant "ppg-verify\n<size:11><i>pre-commit / CI</i></size>" as Verify
end box
box "HTTP — localhost in the PoC,\ncan be a shared remote service" #DAF6F9
  participant "PPG server :8765\n<size:11><i>embedded OPA</i></size>" as PPG <<accent>>
end box

== Session start ==
Guard -> Store : record session_id,\npurge leftover tickets

== Amplified planning ==
User -> Agent : /design-system "build a landing page"
Agent -> MCP : get_platform_guidelines_for_intent
MCP -> PPG : POST /enrich
PPG --> Agent : invariants\n<size:11>(empty: no ADR corpus loaded)</size>

== Plan lock ==
Agent -> MCP : lock_in_plan(structured plan)
MCP -> Store : stamp real session_id
MCP -[#00D2DD]> PPG : POST /register_skill\n<b>SKILL.md + SKILL.rego</b>\n<size:11>(session-scoped upload)</size>
MCP -> PPG : POST /lock_in_plan
PPG -> PPG : OPA: plan-view rules\nfrom the uploaded SKILL.rego

alt <color:#EA4335>plan violates a skill rule</color>
  PPG --> Agent : <color:#EA4335><b>422 PLAN_REJECTED</b></color> {violations}\n<size:11>agent fixes the plan and resubmits</size>
else plan compliant
  PPG --> MCP : <color:#34A853><b>200 PLAN_LOCKED</b></color> + JWT ticket\n{session_id, plan_hash, skill_id, scope}
  MCP -> Store : persist execution_ticket
end

== Governed edits ==
Agent -> Guard : Edit / Write\n<size:11>(PreToolUse fires)</size>
Guard -> Store : load ticket
Guard -> Guard : local checks: signature,\nTTL, path scope, session binding
Guard -[#00D2DD]> PPG : POST /verify_artifact {ticket, path, content}
PPG -> PPG : OPA: artifact-view rules\nfrom the same SKILL.rego

alt artifact compliant
  PPG --> Guard : 200 ARTIFACT_OK
  Guard --> Agent : <color:#34A853><b>exit 0 — edit proceeds</b></color>
else <color:#EA4335>violation</color>
  PPG --> Guard : 422 ARTIFACT_REJECTED
  Guard --> Agent : <color:#EA4335><b>exit 2 — edit blocked</b></color>\n<size:11>OUT_OF_PLAN_SCOPE / SESSION_MISMATCH /</size>\n<size:11>ARCHITECTURAL_INVARIANT_VIOLATION</size>
end

== Apply-time backstop — pre-commit / CI ==
User -> Verify : git commit\n<size:11>(pre-commit hook runs <b>ppg-verify --staged</b>)</size>
Verify -> Store : load ticket of the active session\n<size:11>(same store the MCP wrote to)</size>
Verify -> Verify : git status --porcelain,\nread final file contents
Verify -[#00D2DD]> PPG : POST /verify_changeset\n<size:11>{ticket, files — final states, plan_hash}</size>
PPG -> PPG : OPA: changeset-view rules\nfrom the same SKILL.rego\n<size:11>(selected via ticket claims: session_id, skill_id)</size>

alt changeset compliant
  PPG --> Verify : <color:#34A853><b>OK — commit lands</b></color>
else <color:#EA4335>violation or plan substitution</color>
  PPG --> Verify : <color:#EA4335><b>422 rejected / 409 PLAN_SUBSTITUTION</b></color>
end

note over Guard, PPG #DAF6F9
  The hook and the MCP server never talk to each other: they share
  only the ticket store and the server. All Rego is evaluated server-side —
  in skill-only mode, 100% of the policy comes from the skill package.
  The hook is the fast in-session loop; /verify_changeset is the
  authoritative gate — it re-checks final file states however the bytes got there.
end note

@enduml
